Thoracic vertebrae are distinguished from those of the lumbar region by their smaller vertebral bodies and their characteristically long, slender and inferiorly-oriented spinous processes. In addition, since thoracic vertebrae articulate with the twelve pairs of ribs, there are costal     facets on the bodies and transverse processes of thoracic vertebrae.
